# Staging-first deploy workflow

Unless the user explicitly says otherwise (e.g. "deploy to production", "merge to main", "hotfix to prod"):

## Commits and branches

- Commit and push to the **`staging`** branch (not `main`).
- If work started on another branch, merge or PR into **`staging`** before deploy.
- Do **not** merge to `main` or push production deploys without explicit user approval.

## Deploy target

- **Staging**: `staging.balancewhiz.com` via Render (`family-cash-flow-api-staging`, `family-cash-flow-web-staging`).
- Pushing **`staging`** triggers staging API + static site deploy and GitHub **Staging — build and verify frontend** CI.

## When helping with git/deploy

- Default branch for new commits: **`staging`**
- Default push remote: **`origin staging`**
- After deploy, remind user to smoke-test on **https://staging.balancewhiz.com**
- Production (`main` → balancewhiz.com) only when user explicitly requests it.

## Exceptions (user must say so)

- Urgent production hotfix directly to `main`
- Documentation-only changes user wants on `main` only
- Any task where user names a different branch or environment
